# NestJS patterns — backend

- One feature folder per domain (`leads/`, `properties/`, `health/`) with
  `*.module.ts`, `*.controller.ts`, `*.service.ts`, and `dto/` as needed.
- Controllers stay thin: validate via DTOs + `ValidationPipe`, call the
  service, return the result. No Prisma or `fetch` in controllers.
- DTOs use `class-validator` + `@ApiProperty` for Swagger. Prefer
  `whitelist` / `forbidNonWhitelisted` (already global) — never accept
  undeclared body fields.
- Wire formats that the frontends already consume must stay stable
  (e.g. lead `stage` as the same string union as `LeadStage`; dates as
  `YYYY-MM-DD` strings on the wire).
- Use Nest `Logger` for unexpected failures; never leak stacks to clients
  (global `HttpExceptionFilter` owns the error shape).
- Do not introduce Jest. Tests are Vitest + `unplugin-swc`.
- Do not add auth guards or login flows unless explicitly requested.
